# Architecture Rules

## Folder Structure — Non-Negotiable
```
lib/core/          → constants, theme, router (no business logic)
lib/data/models/   → pure Dart data classes only
lib/data/repositories/ → all Supabase calls live here, nowhere else
lib/data/local/    → Hive cache only
lib/providers/     → all Riverpod providers
lib/screens/       → one folder per screen
lib/widgets/       → reusable widgets only
```
- Screens never call Supabase directly — always through a repository
- Repositories never know about UI — they return models or throw exceptions

## Riverpod
- Use `flutter_riverpod` — no other state solution
- Provider types: `Provider` (sync read-only), `AsyncNotifierProvider` (async with loading/error states), `NotifierProvider` (sync mutable state), `StateProvider` (simple single value)
- Always use `ref.watch` in build, `ref.read` in callbacks
- Never use `ref.watch` inside `initState` or callbacks
- Expose providers at the bottom of the file they belong to
- One provider file per feature domain — no god provider files

## Data Flow
```
UI (screen/widget)
  → watches Provider
    → Provider calls Repository
      → Repository calls Supabase / Hive
```
This is the only allowed direction. Never reverse it.

## Models
- All models are immutable — use `copyWith` for updates
- `fromJson` / `toJson` on every model
- No business logic in models — computed getters only (no side effects)
- Snake_case JSON keys map to camelCase Dart fields

## Navigation
- Use GoRouter only — no `Navigator.push` anywhere
- All routes defined in `lib/core/router/app_router.dart`
- Navigate with `context.go()` or `context.push()`, never `Navigator.of(context)`
- No back navigation mid-game (`/game/*`) — use `PopScope` with exit dialog
